snippet.title: Missing Help Bring Noah & Amber Home !!
snippet.description:
ALL THE INFORMATION IN THIS VIDEO ARE ALLEGED! THIS IS FOR ENTERTAINMENT PURPOSES ONLY! DO NOT TAKE ANYTHING SAID IN THIS VIDEO FOR TRUTH BEFORE YOU DO YOUR OWN RESEARCH! 

Amber & Noah Clare have been missing for a week & their families need help finding them. They were last seen in Tennessee on November 5 with Jacob Clare of Kentucky

Help Support Amber’s Family #BringAmberHome | Ambers Family's GoFundMe Link :  https://www.gofundme.com/f/help-support-ambers-family  

Noah Clare ABDUCTION: Dad in RELATIONSHIP with niece? Please subscribe and ring the bell so you never miss a video!
Missing Person Report

35 year old Jacob Clare has joint custody for his 3 year old son, Noah, with his ex-wife Amanda. Jacob is supposed to get Noah every other weekend, according to custody agreements. One weekend, Amanda dropped him off on Friday, November 5th, and never heard from them again. Jacob’s niece, Amber is also missing, and people believe Jacob may in a relationship with Jacob. Gallatin Police also said that Jacob Clare’s niece Amber Clare, 16, who was reported missing in Beaver Dam, Kentucky, could also be with the pair, WTVC reported. She was last seen on November 5.

Noah is described as 3 feet 5 inches tall and 40 pounds, with brown hair and blue eyes. He was last seen wearing grey sweatpants, a camouflage shirt, and black shoes.

Jacob Clare is 6 feet 7 inches tall and 200 pounds, with brown hair and blue eyes.

The Tennessee Bureau of Investigation has issued an endangered child alert for 3-year-old Noah Clare, who has been missing since November 6. But no amber alert. 

Jacob Clare

Jacob Clare smokes Marlboro 72’s, goes thru about a pack per day. He has a prepaid debit card, we got that from Dollar General around the area, Beaver Dam, he lives around. 

Jacob Clare who is wanted for custodial interference by the Gallatin Police Department.

Sold his old vehicle and bought this one, so he could have extra cash to go on the run. Vehicle could be dumped by now or hidden on the way. Way too tall to fit in car.

The two may be in a silver or grey Subaru Outback.

Jake is familiar with living off the grid. Left him and his niece’s cell phone behind.
